projects.title: The Business Booster by EIT InnoEnergy
projects.description: The new industrial revolution: sustainability, decarbonisation and digitalisation – this is the theme of The Business Booster 2021. THE market place for sustainable energy innovations, The Business Booster is EIT InnoEnergy’s annual flagship event, bringing together 1,200+ attendees from over 40 countries, consisting of start-ups, energy industry representatives, financial communities, policy makers and regulators.

projects.title: Best Stay 2018
projects.description: At Best Stay 2018, we focused on stories about real people, real life examples, real problems and how to solve them. The spotlight was on case studies from Maistra, Valamar, Kempinski, Do&Co Group and many more, who shared their secrets to success. The main topics of the event included education for tourism professionals, new and innovative ways to enhance the guest experience and top revenue trends. Specific areas of the conference programme were dedicated to rewarding guests and staff, finding and mastering the niche market as well as attracting and retaining talent in hospitality.

contributors.headline: Event content producer, currently working on The Economist's Sustainability Week US & Global Trade and Supply Chain Summit

projects.title: Safe Stay 2018
projects.description:
The first edition of Safe Stay 2018 event took place in London at Cavendish Conference Centre on April 27
and gathered professionals who give great importance to safety and security in tourism, who share their
practical knowledge with enthusiasm, who are interested in broadening their insights and keeping
up with new trends to prevent loss and secure their guests. The event was attended by General
Managers, Health and Safety Directors, Managers and Heads of Security, Security consultants...

projects.title: Best Stay 2017
projects.description: The third edition of Best Stay 2017 event was held in a new location, in Split, on October 19-20. With new formats and focus on luxury tourism, during both days, Best Stay attracted more than 250 attendees. The main topics of the event included education for luxury tourism professionals, building a great team to deliver an exceptional guest experience and raising the quality standards in every detail.

projects.title: Smart Public Sector 2017
projects.description: The first ever Smart Public Sector conference was held on March 29-30 at Zagreb and gathered together more than 140 participants. Some of the main topics discussed at the event were the importance of achieving transparency of the public sector and creating user-friendly solutions in order to improve communication with the citizens. During the two days of the conference, all participants had the chance to engage in panel discussions and roundtables, hear case studies of successful examples of modernisation in the sector and take part in 1-2-1 meetings with event partners and sponsors.

projects.title: Best Stay 2016
projects.description:
The second edition of the Best Stay conference was held in Opatija, 17 & 18 November. The event was visited by more than 250 attendees. The main topics of the event included seasonality issues of Croatian tourism, changes and new expectations of today’s guests, design and architecture in the tourism industry as a complement to guest experience, the importance of destination communication
strategies and branding, as well as accommodation and staff branding. At Best Stay 2016, special emphasis was put on the experience of the destination as well as local experience.

Networking programme at Best Stay 2016 conference gave partners and sponsors the opportunity to hold 50+ 1-2-1 meetings and 40+ speed networking meetings.

projects.title: E-GO 2016
projects.description:
The first ever E-GO event was held on May 13th in Poreč, Croatia. The event gathered over 100 attendees including leading e-mobility experts in Croatia and region. Main subjects of the conference emphasized the issuses of developing quality charging infrastructure, financing of electric vehicles, the high initial cost and e-mobility development strategy both for Croatia and the region.
More than 97% of our attendees rated the event organisation as very good and excellent, and more than 80% of the first E-GO event attendees, will take part next year.*

*Results of the feedback form from E-GO 2016

projects.title: Best Stay 2015
projects.description: Best Stay 2015 was a hugely successful event, with over 230 attendees, 56 speakers, many partners and attendees who joined us from all over Croatia, the SSE region and further in Europe. We learnt a great deal, exchanged experiences and had a lot of fun! If your goal is to secure your future tourism revenue today by creating a top quality stay and guest experience far beyond the “sun and sea”, then plan to be there in 2016.

projects.title: TBB.Connect!
projects.description:
TBB.Connect – EIT InnoEnergy’s digital version of the flagship event The Business Booster, took place online from 4-5 November.

Throughout the two days, 1,200 experts from around the world tuned in to take part in 2,100 B2B meetings; view 150 exhibitors, broken down into market segment; watch 120 pitches spanning the entire energy value chain; and hear from guest speakers including Nobel Prize winners, industry experts, policy makers, investors and academics.
